time required: 10 minutes
---

Wash and dry produce. Quarter @lemon{1}. Toast @sourdough bread{4%slices} in a
#toaster{} until golden. Separate @prosciutto{2%ounces} and lay flat on a
work surface; cut horizontally into 1⁄2-inch strips.

In a #medium bowl{}, combine @arugula{2%ounces}, @olive oil{1 1/2%teaspoon},
@salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}, and as much lemon juice as you like.

Spread a thin layer of @ricotta cheese{4%ounces} over toasted sourdough.
Top with arugula mixture, prosciutto strips, and a drizzle of @peach jam{1}.
Sprinkle with as much @chili flakes{1%teaspoon} as you like.

Divide open-faced sandwiches between plates. Serve with any remaining lemon
wedges on the side.